4.74/5  rDev +6.5%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75Dense, dark and viscous, dirty motor-oil like liquid.  Very complex and well balanced flavors.  The cinnamon, the chili peppers, the cocoa and the vanilla all seem to dance around my tongue.  A little less vanilla then the rest but enough to mellow and smooth out the flavor.  Thick, milk shake like feel.  Slight stickiness is welcome as it allows for a prolonged taste on the tongue and second tasting on the lips.  This is one of the best non-BA stouts I've ever had.  Would love to try the BA and coffee versions. 517 charactersbnes09, Jan 04, 2017
